* the risk of debt distress remains high in Burkina Faso, because of a high ratio of net present value of debt. This reflects new debt accumulation, coupled with low exports and moderate growth. This situation calls for vigorous reforms in the export sector, continuous and accelerated improvement of the tax ratio, and strengthening of the quality of institutions that would help enhance borrowing capacity through an increase in the CPIA score (Country Policy and Institutional Assessment).
